The United States congratulates Dr. Mohamed Morsi on his victory in Egypt's Presidential election and commends the Egyptian people for this milestone in their transition to democracy. The US looks forward to working with President-elect Morsi and his government to advance shared interests. It emphasizes the importance of national unity and reaching out to all parties and constituencies in forming a new government. The US also emphasizes the importance of upholding universal values and respecting the rights of all Egyptian citizens, including women and religious minorities. The US intends to sustain its partnership with Egypt as it consolidates its democracy and commends the Presidential Election Commission and the Supreme Council of the Armed Forces for supporting a free and fair election. The US believes it is essential for Egypt to continue playing a role in regional peace, security, and stability. It pledges to stand with the Egyptian people as they pursue democracy, dignity, and opportunity.